Justification: The claim "Ronan does not develop new techniques" is supported by the argument that Ronan increases crop yields (from S2) and the conditional that if Ronan is experienced, he can either increase crop yields or develop new techniques, but not both. Since he increases crop yields, if he were experienced, he would not develop new techniques. However, there is no information that Ronan is experienced, so the conditional does not apply. But from S3, Ronan is dedicated (since he rotates fields and does not use crop rotation). From the statement "Every dedicated farmer either improves their crops or is experienced (or both)," Ronan being dedicated implies he either improves crops or is experienced. Combining with the earlier conditional, if he were experienced, he would not develop new techniques. Even if he is not experienced, he must improve crops, but that does not lead to developing new techniques. The key is that there is no evidence or pathway for Ronan to develop new techniques, and the arguments collectively support that he does not.